Oyo State governor, Seyi Makinde on Wednesday reiterated that the state can pay more than N30,000 as minimum wage for its workforce. Speaking at the Inter-Religious Service to usher the New Year, the governor urged them to be dedicated to work, shun violence and sabotage and also avoid all acts capable of destroying the state. The governor said that there was no worker in the state that would earn below the new national minimum wage approved by the federal government. He said: “We won’t pay in percentages and I want to also state categorically that no worker in Oyo State will earn below the national minimum wage. “Oyo State can pay more than the N30,000.00 minimum wage approved by the federal government. This has not changed. We all can make this happen”, he said. While commending the entire workforce and the good people of the state for their support since inception of this administration, Makinde said, “you have given us “this mandate and we will never take it for granted. We have not come to make people suffer, we have come to ameliorate sufferings. “My plans for the entire citizenry of the state are with good intention that will be impactful into their lives. “The payment of the December salary before the Christmas Day and the 13th Month salary was to ensure the convenience of the entire workforce and have a virile and stable festive period economy. “Like I said, an economy which is being driven by the public service needs the public service to be well funded. This can only be done by the prompt payment of salaries and pensions.’’ 